message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper deals with deep learning for medical imaging, specifically addressing the lack of annotated data for training. This suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of adversarial training and self-regularization also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific application of depth estimation in endoscopy suggests a possible fit with the medical imaging (cs.MED) category. Finally, the use of neural networks in the proposed framework suggests a possible fit with the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEURON) category.
